    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>REMOVAL OF JUDGE SOUGHT</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Amy Harmon</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Harmon, Amy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Defense lawyers ask appellate court to remove Judge Lewis A Kaplan from federal case against Eric Corley; Corley, publisher of magazine 2600, was sued by eight movie studios after he posted program on 2600 Web site that could unscramble encryption on DVD movie discs; defense argues that Kaplan has conflict of interest because he onced worked for New York law firm that represented Warner Brothers, plaintiff in current case, on antitrust matters related to DVD's (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Defense lawyers asked an appellate court yesterday to remove the judge hearing a federal lawsuit against Eric Corley. Mr. Corley, publisher of the magazine 2600, was sued by eight movie studios after he posted a program on the 2600 Web site that could unscramble the encryption on DVD movie discs. The defense argues that Judge Lewis A. Kaplan has a conflict of interest because he once worked at a New York law firm that represented Warner Brothers, a plaintiff in the current case, on antitrust matters related to DVD's. Judge Kaplan had previously denied a motion by the lawyers asking him to recuse himself.</p>
        <p>Amy Harmon</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
